# Admin Portal & Role-Based Access Control System

Add admin portal and RBAC to the existing PDF Form Filler / Internship Logbook SaaS. Firebase Auth is already used for login/registration. This adds Firestore for user management, admin approval workflow, and template access control.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Firebase Service Account Key**: You need to generate a Firebase Admin SDK service account key from the Firebase Console → Project Settings → Service Accounts → Generate New Private Key. This JSON file will be used by the backend to verify tokens and access Firestore. **Never commit this file to git.**

> [!WARNING]
> **Breaking Change — Approval Workflow**: After this change, newly registered users will see a "Waiting for Admin Approval" screen and cannot access the dashboard until an admin approves them. You must manually set the first admin user either via Firebase Console or a one-time setup script (provided).

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Environment Variable Required**: Set `FIREBASE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT` as a stringified JSON env var on Render (paste the entire service account JSON content).

---

## Proposed Changes

### Firebase Admin Backend Config

#### [NEW] [firebase.js](file:///e:/project/Intern-logbook/server/config/firebase.js)
- Initialize Firebase Admin SDK using `FIREBASE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT` env var (JSON string) or a local `serviceAccountKey.json` for development
- Export `admin`, `db` (Firestore), and `auth` (Admin Auth) instances

---

### Auth Middleware

#### [NEW] [auth.js](file:///e:/project/Intern-logbook/server/middleware/auth.js)
- `verifyToken` middleware: Extracts Bearer token from `Authorization` header, verifies via Firebase Admin `auth.verifyIdToken()`, attaches decoded user to `req.user`
- Returns 401 on invalid/missing token

#### [NEW] [adminAuth.js](file:///e:/project/Intern-logbook/server/middleware/adminAuth.js)
- `verifyAdmin` middleware (must run after `verifyToken`): Checks `admins/{uid}` collection in Firestore
- Returns 403 if user is not in admins collection

---

### Admin API Routes

#### [NEW] [admin.js](file:///e:/project/Intern-logbook/server/routes/admin.js)
All routes protected by `verifyToken` + `verifyAdmin` middleware.

| Route | Method | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `/api/admin/users` | GET | List all users with pagination, search, and approved/pending filter |
| `/api/admin/users/:uid/approve` | POST | Set `approved: true` on user doc |
| `/api/admin/users/:uid/reject` | POST | Set `approved: false` on user doc |
| `/api/admin/users/:uid/toggle-active` | POST | Toggle user active status |
| `/api/admin/users/:uid/templates` | PUT | Update `allowedTemplates[]` array |
| `/api/admin/stats` | GET | Return total users, approved, pending counts |
| `/api/admin/setup-first-admin` | POST | One-time setup: creates admin doc for the authenticated user (only works if zero admins exist) |

