## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests (Browser Tests)

1. **Registration + Firestore doc creation**: Register a new user → Verify the user sees the "Waiting for Approval" screen → Verify user cannot access [/app.html](file:///e:/project/Intern-logbook/public/app.html)

2. **Admin login + portal access**: Log in as admin → Navigate to `/admin` → Verify stats and user table render

3. **Approve user flow**: Admin approves a user via admin panel → Log in as that user → Verify they can now access [/app.html](file:///e:/project/Intern-logbook/public/app.html)

4. **Template access control**: Set `allowedTemplates` for a user to only 1 template → Log in as that user → Verify locked templates show lock icon → Verify clicking locked template shows "Access Denied"

5. **Non-admin blocked**: Log in as regular user → Try to navigate to `/admin` → Verify redirect back to [/app.html](file:///e:/project/Intern-logbook/public/app.html)

### Manual Verification
1. Deploy to Render with `FIREBASE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT` env var set
2. Register a new account and confirm the "Waiting for Approval" screen appears
3. Use the `/api/admin/setup-first-admin` endpoint (with bearer token) to make yourself admin
4. Visit `/admin` and approve the new user
5. Log in as the new user and confirm template restrictions work
